n jon hubbard from the mfs investment solutions team will moderate a discussion with mfs chief investment strategist james swanson and mfs chief economist erik weisman as they discuss how to decipher the conflicting narratives being told by the current market landscape  am et   pm bst   pm cest register now view all events dive deeper a culture that works diverse views common values and a team approach to creating better outcomes taking the long view nearly a century of experience understanding the markets and capitalizing on what lies ahead giving back helping our community is as important as building our own business × mfs investment management  wikipedia mfs investment management from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search mfs investment management type subsidiary industry investment management founded  headquarters  huntington avenue boston massachusetts us key people robert manning executive chairman michael roberge ceo president  cio products mutual funds asset management aum us billion april   number of employees  december  parent sun life financial website mfscom mfs investment management mfs is an americanbased global investment manager formerly known as massachusetts financial services founded in  mfs is one of the oldest asset management companies in the world and has been credited with pioneering the mutual fund the very first mutual fund the massachusetts investors trust fund is still in operation today mfs had usd billion in assets under management as of april   contents  history  see also  references  external links historyedit the company was founded in  by l sherman adams charles h learoyd and ashton l carr the companys oldest fund is the massachusetts investors trust a mutual fund created with  at the companys inception and reported to be the worlds first openend investment fund the company used brokerage channels to market its shares to the public and later expanded to  million in assets over the next five years during the stock market crash of  the fund survived an  loss and went on to create a second fund in  by  the massachusetts investors trust fund had become the largest mutual fund in the united states in  mit was reorganized as massachusetts financial services mfs to reflect the firms broadened scope of products and services in  mfs offered one of the nation’s first national municipal bond funds managed municipal bond trust and in  mfs launched the country’s first globally diversified fixedincome fund massachusetts financial international trustbond portfolio in  mfs offered the first closedend highyield municipal bond fund to be traded on the new york stock exchange in  the company was acquired by sun life financial of canada in  mfs chairman and chief executive a keith brodkin died causing a major shift in top management mfss assets under management grew from  billion to  billion between  and  and was reported to be the fastest growing company amongst the twenty largest that funds sold through brokers during the early s mfs and five other mutual fund companies in the boston area were investigated by massachusetts and new hampshire regulators that same year the securities and exchange commission alleged that mfs made false and misleading statements in its fund prospectus about its policy on market trading and market timing mfs paid  million to settle state and federal fraud charges mfs appointed robert pozen as nonexecutive chairman from  to   mfs then implemented a set of company reforms to inform investors about fees keep fund boards independent and create deterrents to market timing these changes were intended to address the concerns of regulators and lawmakers and were praised by fund industry analysts and consumer advocates these reforms ended the softdollar arrangements which allowed the swapping of brokerage commissions for market research and data from  to today assets under management grew from  billion to more than  billioncitation needed headquarters of mfs see alsoedit list of mutualfund families mutual fund referencesedit   innovations   forbescom   mfs corporate fact sheet wwwmfscom   a b c  innovations  december   forbescom retrieved june   amey stone mfs mit a fund that epitomizes longterm investing bloomberg august   retrieved july    andrew caffrey and jeffrey krasner mass nh broaden probe boston globe november   retrieved july   external linksedit company web site retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlemfsinvestmentmanagementoldid categories companies based in bostoninvestment management companies of the united statesmutual fund familiesprivately held companies based in massachusettshidden categories pages using deprecated image syntaxall articles with unsourced statementsarticles with unsourced statements from september  navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction helpabout wikipediacommunity portalrecent changescontact page tools what links hererelated changesupload filespecial pagespermanent linkpage informationwikidata itemcite this page printexport create a bookdownload as pdfprintable version languages españolрусский edit links this page was last edited on  may  at  text is available under the creative commons attributionsharealike license additional terms may apply by using this site you agree to the terms of use and privacy policy wikipedia® is a registered trademark of the wikimedia foundation inc a nonprofit organization privacy policy about wikipedia disclaimers contact wikipedia developers cookie statement mobile view mfs followmfs  twitter skip to content home home home current page moments moments moments current page search query search twitter searches you follow follow following unfollow saved searches remove in this conversation verified accountprotected tweets  suggested